The Senate has commenced the screening of ministerial nominees with a nominee from Abia State, Uchechukwu Ogah. Ogah was ushered into the chamber at 11:20am. First to ask questions was Sen Adamu Aliero (APC,Kebbi). He asked the nominee to speak on how the country’s economy could be diversified. Senator Aliero also ask the nominee to speak on unemployment. Details soon. Uche Sampson Ogah: The ministerial nominee from Abia Lawyer seeks senators’ support for Malami Shehu Sani’s ministerial screening Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin